The Hindu texts describe innumerable universes existing all at the same time, some larger than others, each with its own Brahma administrator with a comparable number of heads. Our universe is described as the smallest with a Brahma of only four heads. 🙏🕉️🚩⛺️

Satya-loka (Brahma-loka)

Tapa-loka

Jana-loka

Mahar-loka

Svar-loka (Svarga-loka or Indra-loka)

Bhuvar-loka

Bhu-loka (Earth plane)

Atala-loka

Vitala-loka

Sutala-loka

Talatala-loka

Mahatala-loka

Rasatala-loka

Patala-loka

The Hindu concept of innumerable universes is comparable to the multiverse theory, except nonparallel where individual jiva-atmas (embodied souls) exist in exactly one universe at a time. All universes manifest from the same matter, and so they all follow parallel time cycles, manifesting and unmanifesting at the same time 🙏🕉️🚩⛺️
